        },
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> empty cmd is only allowed when there is only a range or only a modifier. That's why you're seeing the error. not sure if allowing empty cmd commands without any other content is allowed at the API level. The API differs from the traditional cmd.\r\n\r\nMy reasoning is that any valid content of command line (i.e. typing it in command line and pressing `<CR>` doesn't result in an error) should be parsed with `nvim_parse_cmd()`. Typing `:<CR>` does not result in an error, so probably should return \"no command\" object. The same for any number whitespaces (`:<Space><CR>`), by the way.\r\n\r\nTo be fair, this is minor adjustment. It *can* be guarded on the user side, just adds inconvenience.",
            "created_at": "2025-12-01T09:57:05Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36665#issuecomment-3595626218",
